SCALE LAW (NON-NEGOTIABLE — VERIFY AGAINST HUMANS AND TRUCK): Every firewood bag is a rectangular prism with edge lengths only 40 cm, 30 cm, and 10 cm.
Standing upright: 40 cm tall × 30 cm wide × 10 cm deep (10 cm = narrow thickness, front-to-back).
Lying flat (largest face down): footprint 40 cm × 30 cm, and the vertical height of the bag above the ground must read VERY FLAT — the 10 cm edge is the thickness dimension and in real handling these packs compress; render them as flat as credible: ~8–10 cm tall in side profile with at most +1 cm extra for slight mesh tension over wood — total side height not to exceed ~11 cm. Forbidden: thick puffy slabs, double-thick “pillow” stacks, 15–25 cm tall flat layers, squashy loaf shapes. Think dense plank / thick pizza-box, not cushion.
No cube bags, no spherical bags.
Sanity checks: (1) Hand span ~18–22 cm — 30 cm bag width > one hand, < two. (2) Standing 40 cm < pickup tyre outer diameter (~70–80 cm). (3) Two standing stacked ≈ 80 cm; three ≈ 120 cm (sternum zone, not over head). (4) Flat stack of 4 layers should only add ~32–44 cm total height — if it looks half a person tall, wrong.
If a flat bag reads as thick as a standing bag’s 40 cm height, the image is wrong.

CRITICAL — WOOD STAYS INSIDE BAGS ONLY:
All firewood is inside closed milky-white mesh sacks. No loose splits, rounds, wedges, bark, or kindling on bed, tailgate, ground, or in hands — only soft, milky suggestion of mass through the weave (dark/light banding), not sharp exterior log geometry. No open, torn, or dumping bags.

Square 16:9 or 3:2 photoreal 8K, documentary–advertising hybrid, South African estate / driveway / yard, late afternoon golden hour, long warm shadows. Bakkie offload: 2–4 workers moving only mesh bags from load bed to ground. No readable text, logos, watermarks, legible plates, branded clothes.

CAMERA (NOT DRONE, NOT CLOSE-UP):
Ground height ~1.45–1.65 m. Medium-wide: most of load bed, full rear wheel, part of cab, ≥2 full figures. ~10–18 m subject distance, FF equiv ~28–50 mm, straight verticals, deep documentary DOF (truck, bags, faces/hands sharp; distant BG soft). No fisheye, no aerial, no f/0.95 product isolation.

VEHICLE:
SA-common pickup silhouette (no badges). Tailgate down/open. Tyres ~70–80 cm — scale anchor vs 40 cm standing bag and ~8–11 cm flat bag height.

BAGS — MATERIAL:
Milky semi-translucent white woven PP, tight weave, matte, not orange net. Opaque white header, oval die-cut handle where seen. Rammed full but envelope obeys dimensions; flat orientation = emphatically LOW PROFILE. Inside: horizontal-layer stack read through mesh; not vertical pencils.

STACKING ON THE VEHICLE — NEAT BUT NOT CGI-PERFECT:
Bags in the bed are clearly a professional delivery load: rows and columns make sense, weight low and stable, nothing chaotic or “fucked” — not spilled, not random avalanche.
However — not a laser-perfect 3D array: allow small believable irregularities: one bag 2–4 cm out of line, a corner slightly kicked, a row height mismatch of one bag thickness, a gentle lean into its neighbour, a finger-width gap between two bags, top layer with one piece not perfectly flush but still safe and square.
Avoid: mathematical clone grid, every seam aligned to pixel, symmetrical pyramid that looks rendered, identical bag angles.
Goal: competent human stacked — tidy yard delivery, not factory sim, not mess.

GROUND STACK (IF SHOWN):
Bags placed on paving / gravel — same neat-but-human rules: stable rectangles, slight misalignment OK, flat bags stay LOW (8–11 cm profile).

WORKERS — REAL, GRITTY:
2–4 diverse South African adults, asymmetric stances, knees bent, gripping 30 cm width with credible hand span. Skin: pores, uneven tone, sun, no wax. Sweat: forehead/temples/neck sheen, damp underarms/back, optional single droplet — tasteful. Dirt: dust on boots, knees, bag bottoms, smudge on forearm, fingernail edge dirt. Hands: veins, creases, grip redness, no manicured. Clothes: faded plain tees/jeans, wear, dusty hems; scuffed boots/sneakers. Faces: concentration / exertion, not catalogue smiles, not all looking at camera.

POSE / LIGHT / ENV:
Single sun direction, consistent shadows. Hard low sun, ground bounce fill, dust motes optional in backlight. Paved or compacted gravel, dry heat haze far BG only. No HDR halos, no glamour skin.

HARD BAN

Loose wood outside bags; torn/open bags; thick flat bags reading >~12 cm tall; puffy mattress layers; hyper-perfect bed stacking; drone; fisheye; giant/tiny bags; orange mesh; readable brands; plastic skin; identical poses; snow; European forest.

NEGATIVE (append)

loose logs, wood on ground, open bag, torn mesh, thick flat sack, puffy bag, double-thick layer, 15cm+ flat height, cushion bag, loaf-shaped bag, oversize bag, toy bag, perfect CGI grid stack, laser-aligned bags, clone symmetry, drone, aerial, fisheye, orange net, red mesh, readable text, logo, watermark, legible plate, airbrushed skin, HDR halos, cartoon, low-res, pine rounds, birch, any bark outside white mesh